    "message_1": "Given the following set of data:\n(0, 1), (1, 3), (2, 8), (3, 18), (4, 35)\n\nUse Lagrange polynomials to estimate the value at x=2.5.",
    "message_2": "To estimate the value at x=2.5 using Lagrange polynomials, we will use the formula:\n\nP(x) = L0(x) * y0 + L1(x) * y1 + L2(x) * y2 + L3(x) * y3 + L4(x) * y4\n\nWhere Lk(x) are the Lagrange basis polynomials and (xk, yk) are the given data points.\n\nLk(x) = Π((x - xi) / (xk - xi)) for i = 0 to n, i ≠ k\n\nLet's calculate the Lagrange basis polynomials for our given data points:\n\nL0(x) = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((0 - 1) * (0 - 2) * (0 - 3) * (0 - 4))\nL1(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((1 - 0) * (1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4))\nL2(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((2 - 0) * (2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4))\nL3(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 4)) / ((3 - 0) * (3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4))\nL4(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3)) / ((4 - 0) * (4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3))\n\nNow, we will substitute x = 2.5 into the Lagrange basis polynomials:\n\nL0(2.5) = ((2.5 - 1) * (2.5 - 2) * (2.5 - 3) * (2.5 - 4)) / ((0 - 1) * (0 - 2) * (0 - 3) * (0 - 4)) = 0.375\nL1(2.5) = ((2.5 - 0) * (2.5 - 2) * (2.5 - 3) * (2.5 - 4)) / ((1 - 0) * (1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4)) = -0.5\nL2(2.5) = ((2.5 - 0) * (2.5 - 1) * (2.5 - 3) * (2.5 - 4)) / ((2 - 0) * (2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4)) = 2.25\nL3(2.5) = ((2.5 - 0) * (2.5 - 1) * (2.5 - 2) * (2.5 - 4)) / ((3 - 0) * (3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4)) = -1.5\nL4(2.5) = ((2.5 - 0) * (2.5 - 1) * (2.5 - 2) * (2.5 - 3)) / ((4 - 0) * (4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3)) = 0.375\n\nFinally, we will substitute the Lagrange basis polynomials and the given y-values into the formula:\n\nP(2.5) = L0(2.5) * y0 + L1(2.5) * y1 + L2(2.5) * y2 + L3(2.5) * y3 + L4(2.5) * y4\nP(2.5) = 0.375 * 1 + (-0.5) * 3 + 2.25 * 8 + (-1.5) * 18 + 0.375 * 35\nP(2.5) = 0.375 + (-1.5) + 18 + (-27) + 13.125\nP(2.5) = 3\n\nSo, the estimated value at x = 2.5 using Lagrange polynomials is 3."
